Deputy National Security Advisor Daleep Singh, along with National Security Council Senior Director for Africa Dana Banks and Deputy Assistant Secretary of State for African Affairs Amy Holman, will be traveling to the Democratic Republic of the Congo. This visit highlights the Biden Administration's commitment to collaborating with African nations to address global challenges and promote shared interests. During their time in the Democratic Republic of the Congo, Singh will meet with senior government officials to discuss areas of cooperation in addressing climate change and the COVID-19 pandemic, establishing resilient supply chains, and attracting more U.S. and international investment. Afterward, Singh will travel to Berlin, Germany to participate in the first G7 Sherpa Meeting of the German 2022 G7 Presidency.